div1.p:
In the District Court, holding Terms at Seattle
In the matter of the application of Jeremiah Mangan for a Writ of Habeas Corpus This cause coming in to the heard on the writ of habeas corpus heretofore issued herein and the return of John H McGraw thereto, and is apposing from said return that said Jeremiah Mangan is unlawfully retrained of his liberty by said John H McGraw and the in is undone that said Jeremiah Mangan he and is hereby discharged from custody, and said John H McGraw is hereby ordered to release said Jeremiah Mangan from all restraint, provinced however that this only shall not wherate to protect nor shall in the a bar to the further prosecution for the same alleged offense for which he was committed by virtue of the commitment referred to in the return of said John H McGraw Said in when Court this 18th day of May A. D. 1889
R- 6867 District Court Application of J. Mangan for writ of H. C WRIT
